		<div class="comment_header">
		Comment <a href="#c_1713651573">19</a> by Raymond Camden
		posted on 2/2/2008 at 12:29 AM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>Unfortunately no. I can say that I too am learning ColdSpring. There is indeed a simple way to do basic stuff like DSN, etc. Consider this bean def:</p><p>&lt;bean id="config" class="ModelGlue.Bean.CommonBeans.SimpleConfig"&gt;<br>	&lt;property name="config"&gt;<br>		&lt;map&gt;<br>			&lt;entry key="dsn"&gt;<br>			&lt;value&gt;foo&lt;/value&gt;<br>			&lt;/entry&gt;<br>		&lt;/map&gt;<br>	&lt;/property&gt;<br>&lt;/bean&gt;</p><p>You can imagine more settings in here as well. You can then pass this bean to a CFC:</p><p>&lt;bean id="answerDAO" class="foo.model.dao.answerdao"&gt;<br>	&lt;constructor-arg name="config"&gt;&lt;ref bean="config" /&gt;&lt;/constructor-arg&gt;<br>&lt;/bean&gt;</p><p>And in your CFC do:</p><p>&lt;cffunction name="init" access="public" output="false" returnType="answerdao"&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="config" type="any" required="true"&gt;<br>	&lt;cfset variables.dsn = arguments.config.getConfigSetting("dsn")&gt;<br>	&lt;cfreturn this&gt;<br>&lt;/cffunction&gt;</p></div>
	</div>
</div>
		
